cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on cooperative cognitive radio networks and analyzes packet throughput of primary and secondary users. This falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper employs a signal flow graph-based approach to obtain closed-form expressions of packet throughput. This involves the use of information theory concepts and techniques.
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Cognitive radio networks involve the sharing of spectrum resources and require security measures to prevent unauthorized access. The paper may discuss security aspects of the proposed cooperation method.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper may involve the use of control theory techniques to optimize the transmission probability of secondary users and ensure stability of the system.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper may discuss the impact of interference on multimedia transmission in cognitive radio networks and how the proposed cooperation method can improve throughput performance.
